cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

The paper discusses the use of machine learning for network security, specifically for 5G networks. This makes it likely to fall under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of machine learning also suggests a possible fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to network security, which could potentially fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
